briefdescription.para: Look up a tensor by name and return a weight view describing how to read it.

detaileddescription.para: Lookup a tensor by name and return a uniform view.

For deduplicated tensors, the returned view points at:
a defaults byte-range (base tensor data),
a bitmask indicating which elements are overridden,
an exceptions stream providing the replacement values.
If a tensor has no mask/exceptions, the view is returned as IE_WVIEW_DIRECT.

briefdescription.para: Set an int4 nibble into a packed byte array (lo/hi nibbles).
Materialize a weight view into a contiguous destination buffer.

detaileddescription.para: Materialize a weight view into a contiguous buffer (lossless).

Behavior:
If view is IE_WVIEW_DIRECT, this copies the referenced bytes verbatim.
If view is IE_WVIEW_DEDUP:
For non-int4 dtypes: copy defaults, then apply per-element overrides from the exceptions stream where the mask bit is set.
For int4: destination is a packed nibble array; defaults are copied, then overridden nibble-by-nibble from the exceptions stream.
The function returns 0 on any validation/size error.

simplesect.para: Number of bytes written to dst, or 0 on failure.

briefdescription.para: Lossless deduplicated-weights loader implementation.

detaileddescription.para:
Design goals:
mmap-friendly: map large blobs once, return pointer views
low overhead lookup: sorted tensor table + binary search
lossless: exact reconstruction via mask + exceptions stream

This module intentionally uses a minimal, self-contained JSON scanner that supports the subset of JSON needed for model.dedup.json. This avoids hard dependencies on external JSON libraries and keeps build integration simple.
Expected JSON shape (subset):

{ "files": { "defaults": "model.defaults.bin", "exceptions": "model.exceptions.bin", "masks": "model.masks.bin" }, "tensors": [ { "name": "layers.0.attn.q_proj.weight", "dtype": "fp16", "shape": [4096, 4096], "default": {"file":"defaults", "offset":123, "nbytes":456}, "mask": {"file":"masks", "offset":789, "nbytes":1011}, "exceptions": {"file":"exceptions", "offset":1213,"nbytes":1415} } ] }

Mask semantics:
bit=1 indicates an exception element is present and consumed from exceptions stream.
For int4, elements are nibbles in row-major order (index i maps to byte i/2, nibble i%2).
